# T14-docked — laptop lid OPEN, external HDMI monitor connected.
# autorandr matches profiles by EDID (the 'setup' file), so this profile
# cannot be fabricated: it must be saved on the T14 with the monitor plugged.
# autorandr ignores this file (only 'config', 'setup', and hook scripts matter),
# so it is safe to leave here as a reminder. Delete it after saving if you like.
#
# Layout (from the old bin/monitors-config): HDMI primary, left of the laptop.
#
# 1. Plug the monitor, lid open, then set the layout:
#      xrandr --output HDMI-1 --primary --auto --left-of eDP-1 --output eDP-1 --auto
#
# 2. Capture it (writes real 'config' + 'setup' here, overwriting nothing important):
#      autorandr --save T14-docked
#
# 3. Copy the saved profile back into the repo (the live dir is a throwaway
#    stow copy, wiped by reload-environment):
#      cp -r ~/.config/autorandr/T14-docked ~/environment/dotfiles/config/.config/autorandr/
#
# 4. Commit.
